cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless networking and resource allocation, which falls under this category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a scheduling policy that aims to maximize the aggregate throughput, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of the proposed scheduling policy on the quality of experience (QoE) of multimedia service delivery. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel scheduling policy that aims to improve the performance of cells with a high discrepancy in SNR distribution, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography or security, it is possible that the proposed scheduling policy may have implications for the security of wireless networks, as interference allocation can affect the confidentiality and integrity of wireless transmissions.
